Material at your disposal
This course contains: video lectures, non graded "in video questions," four graded quizzes (imperative), and lab session to learn how to code with Python. 
You will use the "In Video Questions" and lab sessions to ensure grasp of the concepts covered in each video. And you will rely on the lab sessions to develop programming skills.
The graded quizzes will enable you to asses your mastering of the concepts. 
Should it be your first steps with Python, you will  find in this first module a video explaining how to install Anaconda.
If you are new to Python, you will also find 7 additional videos on our website that will help as a "crash course" to help you get started with Python. You can get started by copying the following link in your browser:

